The paper deals with the recovery of sparse signals from few observations, which is a problem in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SP (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the thresholded Landweber iterations, which is a method in numerical analysis and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely sub-category as well. The experimental evaluation of the proposed algorithm involves solving optimization problems, which falls under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
